main event: Numerous fishing vessels off the West Coast of Florida observed a brilliant flare moving in a southeast direction.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 30-40 minutes,The flare was noted by several fishing vessels in the area,Miami Coast Guard indicated the flare was associated with missile test activity at Cape Canaveral,The object was observed at a bearing of 085 degrees,The report indicates that the object could possibly be a balloon, aircraft, or a missile, but insufficient data prevents a clear conclusion.
location: West Coast of Florida, Florida, US
